    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>This code throws the following exceptions:</p>

&lt;?php

require_once "Zend/Currency.php";

var_dump(new Zend_Currency('LVL', 'et_EE')); // Works as expected
var_dump(new Zend_Currency('LVL', 'lv_LV')); // Zend_Currency_Exception: Currency 'LVL' not found in..
var_dump(new Zend_Currency('LVL', 'lt_LT')); // Zend_Currency_Exception: Currency 'LVL' not found in..

?&gt;

<p>Apparently locale data is missing for the currency 'LVL' (Latvian Lats) both in the Latvian locale (lv_LV) and in Lithuanian locale (lt_LT).</p>

<p>On closer inspection, lv.xml does contain  but it only contains the  element. Adding an appropriate  elements solves the problem.</p>

<p>lt.xml does not contain any data for LVL.</p>

